-- Italian Police Arrest Five People in Railway Contract Kickbacks Probe
-- Marco Bertacche
-- 2010-07-06T09:54:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/italian-police-arrest-five-people-in-railway-contract-kickbacks-probe.html

          
          
             Italy’s finance police arested five
people, including executives of the country’s state railway
company Trenitalia, for alleged kickbacks for maintenance
contracts, according to an e-mailed statement.  
 Trenitalia cooperated in the investigation and dismissed
the executives, the statement said.  
          
          


  


        